ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The boughs from a stand of trees mingle to form a natural umbrella that is alive with the sounds of tiny songbirds. A group of small animals sip delicately from a tiny pond that sparkles in the small streams of light that reach through the interwoven branches. Beside it sits a stone bowl atop a polished wooden stump. The animals are seemingly oblivious to the entrance of anyone into their domain, intent only upon enjoying the nature around them. An opening leads back to the garden.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 448
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=2573
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The smooth bowl shines with polished brilliance, sending off waves of clean nature power.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
	ADD bivyar 1
	IFVAR bivyar = 1
		ECHO ALL A small elderly man walks out from behind the trees, his eyes crinkling merrily, and sits down on the stump regarding you with a curious gaze.
		GENMON 300
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY hello
	ECHO ALL The little man smiles and nods at you by way of greeting, "Honor be to your family, I am Biv'yar'pirh."
ENDIF
IFSAY ruined_world?
	ECHO ALL The little man sighs, a deep sadness passing over his features, "Yes, this is our world. A world where nature has retreated from the advance of technology gone rampantly berserk. From their tombs of steel in the mountain city of Yirak'Nor, the Lords of Rha'zka'urnik send their evil machines against us, seeking to destroy all vestiges of beauty and nature."
ENDIF
IFSAY nature?
	ECHO ALL The little man smiles sadly as he looks around this little piece of nature, "We are one of the communities who seek to fight back against the scourge of the Rha'zka'urnik. We seek to preserve what we can, but fight a losing fight."
ENDIF
IFSAY rha'zka'urnik?
	ECHO ALL The man's eyes grow dark, "They are the ones who control the machines, in fact they are machines themselves. Many years ago the machines where given the ability to think for themselves, in time they grew arrogant and decided that they were the ones to rule this world. They took control of all machines and sent them out against humans in a war of annihilation. Weapons of mass destruction were used, turning the land into a barren wasteland. We still fight, but it is becoming a fight without hope."
ENDIF
IFSAY twelve?
	ECHO ALL The man chuckles slightly, "A myth of hope. It is said that a council of twelve loremasters saw what was to come, in their wisdom they created the Twelve Great Lores and hid them across the land, in the hope that they would be found and used in the healing of the world. But, it is only a myth."
ENDIF
IFSAY complex?
	ECHO ALL The man furrows his brow, "We do not know what it was, we think that it was the military base for a nation of the ancients."
ENDIF
IFSAY ancients?
	ECHO ALL The man gestures, as if to wave away the question, "The ancients are those who built the machines, we do not speak of them."
ENDIF
IFSAY seeker?
	ECHO ALL The man growls, "Killers, made with metal parts, some melded with flesh, who wander the wasteland searching for communities such as these. When they find them they are programmed to destroy them."
ENDIF
;
MACRO 81
IFPREVERB SKIN -1
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR ORG = 7
		IFVAR SKILL32 < 5
			RANDOM dummy1 1 100 0
			ADD dummy1 AGI
			IFVAR dummy1 => 215
				ECHO PLAYER You skillfully reach inside the large metal corpse and remove some bullets from the ammunition feed belt.
				ECHO OTHERS %N reaches into the large metal corpse and removes something from inside it.
				NEWITEM 8 1065
			ELSE
				ECHO PLAYER You curse as you bungle the attempt to get something from inside the large metal corpse.
				ECHO OTHERS %N curses as %s bungles an attempt to remove something from inside the corpse.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
		IFVAR SKILL32 => 5
			RANDOM dummy1 1 100 0
			ADD dummy1 AGI
			IFVAR dummy1 => 215
				ECHO PLAYER You skillfully reach inside the large metal corpse and remove a clip from the ammunition feed belt.
				ECHO OTHERS %N reaches into the large metal corpse and removes something from inside it.
				NEWITEM 8 1756
			ELSE
				ECHO PLAYER You curse as you bungle the attempt to get something from inside the large metal corpse.
				ECHO OTHERS %N curses as %s bungles an attempt to remove something from inside the corpse.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
